  <text>
      <body>
        
     
      <div xml:id="Sonnet41"> 
              <interpGrp type="poembox">
                <interp ana="#form" type="free"></interp>
                <interp ana="#tone" type="sad"></interp>
                <interp ana="#topic" type="death"></interp>
              </interpGrp>
             <lg> 
              <l>Now his body is a uniform</l>
          <l>All the colors have bled</l> 
          <l>from the gray flag of his face.</l>
          <l>He was badly led to this sprawl,</l>
          <l>whether by Ike or Priam</l>
          <l>The curly burst to the summer street.</l>
          <l>The pain in the groin from the teasing girl.</l>
          <l>The pint passed behind the stands.</l>
          <l>His being!</l>
          <l>The unblessed seeds of his dead children.</l>
          <l>He was badly taught to speak out his throat,</l>
          <l>in our bad silence.</l>
          <l>All his leaders follow</l>
          <l>where his torn body points down.</l>
          <l>Now his body is a uniform.</l>
